nt||at|mitche: The rule of 10 and 12 was proposed by Ron Klinger and you can google it. 
The basic idea is -  count the number of trumps you have and the number of tricks they are contracting for. 
If the total is at least 12, you meet part 1 of the rule of 10 and 12
Second, count the number of trump tricks you expect to win, and add that number to the level 
-- if that total is at least 10, you meet the requirements of the rule of 10 and 12|
